title: Quiet Talks on Prayer
creator: S. D. Gordon
description: LibriVox recording of Quiet Talks on Prayer, by S. D. Gordon. Read by David Barnes. An open life, an open hand, open upward, is the pipe line of communication between the heart of God and this poor befooled old world. Our prayer is God's opportunity to get into the world that would shut Him out. (From the first chapter). For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
